Great service and great food. I've never had a bad experience at either of the locations I've been to. Iron age offers all the benefits of all you can eat restaurants, without the pitfalls. As someone who is Korean living in DC, I feel like you have to venture out all the way into the VA or MD suburbs to get a legit Korean dining experience since all of the "Korean" places in DC are catered towards non-Korean palates and are over priced. This Iron Age, like the ones in Rockville and Annandale, is super legit. Service was great and you really can't beat the price for all-you-can-eat. I also didn't feel unsafe dining inside. Highly recommend.

Health safety precautions were amazing! Our temperatures were taken and hand sanitizer provided before we could be seated and each table was more than appropriately distanced. The waitstaff also did a good job of redirecting people outside if they didn’t read the signs. Also, a foot handle was implemented in the washrooms so that customers don’t have to use their hands to touch anything after washing their hands. Last but not least, the food was extremely enjoyable and the wait staff was appropriately attentive. Definitely plan on coming back!
